-- China posts $670 million trade surplus in Q1: Xinhua
-- 
-- Mon Apr 9, 2012 11:30pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/04/10/us-china-economy-xinhua-idUSBRE83903P20120410

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - China posted a trade surplus of $670 million in the first quarter, state news agency Xinhua said on Tuesday minutes before the release of the country's official monthly trade report. 
 Xinhua said Chinese exports rose 9.8 percent in March from a year ago on a calendar adjusted basis. (Reporting by Zhou Xin and Koh Gui Qing; Editing by Don Durfee)